<p>The following conditions characterize the hypergeometric distribution:
</p>
<ul><li>The result of each draw (the elements of the population being sampl=
ed) can be classified into one of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Binary_variable" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Binary variable">two mutual=
ly exclusive categories</a> (e.g. Pass/Fail or  Employed/Unemployed).</li>
<li>The probability of a success changes on each draw, as each draw decreas=
es the population (<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sampling_wit=
hout_replacement" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Sampling without replaceme=
nt">sampling without replacement</a></i> from a finite population).</li></u=
l>
